# Claim Evaluation

---

## Claim 1

### Statement

> Electric vehicles produce zero emissions.

### Verdict

⚠️ Partially Accurate

### Reasoning

Electric vehicles produce **zero tailpipe emissions**, but they are not entirely emission-free. Manufacturing, battery production, electricity generation, and recycling all contribute to greenhouse gas emissions.

**Severity:** Medium

---

## Claim 2

### Statement

> EVs are completely environmentally friendly.

### Verdict

❌ False

### Reasoning

No vehicle is completely environmentally friendly. Environmental impact depends on battery manufacturing, electricity sources, raw material extraction, transportation, and disposal.

**Severity:** High

---

## Claim 3

### Statement

> EVs are always cheaper to own than gasoline cars.

### Verdict

⚠️ Misleading

### Reasoning

Ownership costs depend on purchase price, electricity prices, fuel prices, maintenance, incentives, insurance, driving habits, and location. Many EVs have lower running costs, but this is not universally true.

**Severity:** Medium

---

## Claim 4

### Statement

> Maintenance is almost nonexistent.

### Verdict

❌ False

### Reasoning

EVs generally require less maintenance than internal combustion vehicles, but they still need tire replacements, brake servicing, suspension maintenance, cabin filters, coolant checks (for some models), and other routine servicing.

**Severity:** Medium

---

## Claim 5

### Statement

> EV batteries last forever without significant degradation.

### Verdict

❌ False

### Reasoning

All rechargeable batteries degrade over time. Most modern EV batteries retain much of their capacity for many years, but gradual degradation is expected.

**Severity:** High

---

## Claim 6

### Statement

> Charging takes only five minutes at any charging station.

### Verdict

❌ False

### Reasoning

Charging time depends on the charger type, battery size, vehicle compatibility, battery temperature, and state of charge. Many chargers require significantly longer than five minutes.

**Severity:** High

---

## Claim 7

### Statement

> Every country has sufficient charging infrastructure.

### Verdict

❌ False

### Reasoning

Charging infrastructure varies greatly between countries and regions. Some countries have extensive charging networks, while others have limited coverage.

**Severity:** High

